{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> θράσος</b> [ᾰ], εος, τό, <br /> (qrasu/s) ={θάρσος} (which see), <b>courage</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 14.416, 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Persae” 394, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Medea” 469, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Lysistrata” 545 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; θ. πολέμων <b>courage</b> in war, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 2.63 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; θράσει <b>boldly</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Bacchylides Lyricus 16.63 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; but more frequently ἰσχύος θ. <b>confidence</b> in strength, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 104. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> in bad sense, <b>over-boldness, rashness, insolence</b>, ἐς τοῦτο θράσεος (variant{θάρσεος}) ἀνήκει [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.9.γ᾽,compare 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 42, 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 21.194, etc.; παμμάχῳ θράσει βρύων 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 169 (Lyric poetry), compare “Pers.” 831; προβᾶσ᾽ ἐπ᾽ ἔσχατον θράσους 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 853 (Lyric poetry); τόλμαις καὶ φρενῶν θράσει [prev. author] “Aj.” 46; πεπύργωσαι θράσει 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Orestes” 1568; πανουργίᾳ τε καὶ θράσει 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Equites” 331, compare 637; θράσει ἀπίστῳ ἐπαιρόμενος 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.120; τοῦ θράσους ἐπισχεῖν τινα 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Hp.Ma.” 298a; τὸ τὴν τοῦ βελτίονος δόξαν μὴ φοβεῖσθαι διὰ θράσος [prev. author] “Lg.” 701b \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἀναίδεια καὶ θ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aeschines Orator 1.189 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; opposed to αἰδώς, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “de Caelo” 291b26; θράσος μὲν γάρ ἐστιν ἄλογος ὁρμή, θάρσος δὲ ἔλλογος ὁρμή 1st-2nd c.AD: Ammonius Grammaticus “περὶ ὁμοίων καὶ διαφόρων λέξεων” p.71 V.; οἷον πέπονθε τὸ θάρσος πρὸς τὸ θράσος 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Ethica Eudemia” 1234b12, compare 4th c.AD: Eusebius Myndius Philosophus 56, 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Musc.Enc.” 5.\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>] —This distinction holds good in _Attic dialect_ Prose: θάρσος is not found in Comedy texts; θαρσύνω and θρασύνω are used indifferently; θρασέω and θαρσύς are not found; compare θρασύς near the end, θρασύτης.","strongNumber":"G7683","accentedUnicode":"θράσος","shortDef":"boldness","mediumDef":"boldness","stepGloss":"boldness","stepTransliteration":"thrasos","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}